pageContext.description: Dimension: L 124.2mm; We 65.1; Wm 41.8; Bm 44.1; Blp 11.8; DS 86,Typology: lower m-m pronounced rib; narrow rect. flat s. end,Manufacture: sl. anomalous bulge on rev. face of m-m apparently slight dislocation between two mould valves; cg. fl. - parts rounded crested, ? untrimmed, others flattened with irreg. lipping; hole in body face with rounded edges - cg. flaw; stump of fairly thick cg. fl. round s.m. - part broken sur., part hammered with assoc. lipping - int. & ext.; poor metal flaw above hole - no. of fissures; s. core misplaced - off centre; small half-moon depressions in one face seem like anc. pmks.,Attached Material: white and light brown deposits
pageContext.surface: dark brown to gold patina; subst. areas with variable white green - bright green textured sur.
